<HEAD>Daylight Time: Spring Forward</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Set your clock ahead an hour before retiring
tonight.
   Most of the nation returns to daylight time at 2 a.m. Sunday,
gaining an hour of evening light for cookouts and recreation.
   Daylight time will remain in effect until Oct. 30 this year,
when that hour of lost sleep will be returned.
