<HEAD>Owner Sells Radio Station After 24 Years Of Runng It Alone</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GLOUCESTER, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Simon Geller, who owned and operated
WVCA-FM by himself for 24 years from his home in this coastal
community, has sold the station.
   Geller, 68, said Thursday he has signed a contract with an
unidentified buyer for the station he has owned since 1964. He
declined to disclose details, saying only that a report of a $1
