<HEAD>Dollar, Stocks Slip in Tokyo</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES with closing dollar, stocks. EDITS to conform. No
pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices fell moderately Friday and the dollar
lost ground against the Japanese yen in Tokyo trading.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues fell 156.04 points, or 0.59 percent, to close the
day at 26,104.22 points.
   The dollar closed Friday at 124.10 yen, down 0.40 yen from
yesterday`s close of 124.50 yen.
   ``Nothing is happening here,'' said a dealer at a major U.S.
securities firm, speaking on condition of anonymity. ``It's the
Easter holiday and people are not doing anything.''
   The dealer said the dollar rebounded slightly following moderate
intervention by the Bank of Japan to prop up the sagging currency.
The bank does not publicly comment on its market activities.
   A trader at a major commercial bank in Tokyo said local market
participants are anticipating a weak dollar in the new 1988 fiscal
year which began Friday. Major stock markets around the world are
closed Friday.
