<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Philippines-Violence     04-01 0168</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Philippines-Violence,0172</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Farmer Goes on Rampage, Kills Four, Wounds Four Others</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ZAMBOANGA CITY, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A farmer armed with a 10-inch
knife went berserk and killed four neighbors and wounded four
others before a crowd stoned him to death, the military said today.
   Philippine Constabulary operations chief Maj. German Doria
identified the man as Pablo Bingcoy, 33. He said the attack
occurred Thursday in the village of Mangangaon in Zamboanga del
Norte province, 450 miles south of Manila.
   Doria said Bingcoy had fasted and prayed for several days in
hopes of earning an amulet, which he believed would make him
invincible.
   Then Bingcoy took a 10-inch long knife, went out of the house
and attacked everyone he saw. Doria said Bingcoy first killed a
neighbor's pig. Then after a heated argument, Bingcoy killed the
owner, his wife and 6-year-old son.
   Afterwards, he stabbed five people, one of whom died later in a
hospital, Doria said. An angry mob then stoned Bingcoy to death,
the major said.
</TEXT>
