<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Korea-BusCrash     04-01 0155</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Korea-Bus Crash,0160</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>20 Dead in Bus Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus careened off a road while
crossing a bridge and plunged into an icy river in the capital
today, killing at least 20 people and injuring 40, police said.
   Many of the victims were high school students returning home.
   Police said the accident occurred shortly after 5 p.m. in the
eastern part of the capital when the bus blew a front tire and the
driver lost control.
   The bus, carrying more than 60 passengers, fell 24 feet into the
Han River, police said.
   Policemen and passersby rescued about 10 people who broke
windows and climbed onto the top of the mangled bus, they said.
Divers pulled 20 bodies from the frigid waters and continued to
search for victims in the partly submerged vehicle.
   Police said the bus may have been speeding when the accident
occurred. They gave no other details.
 
</TEXT>
