<1ST_LINE>r a PM-MissingEinstein     04-01 0159</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Missing Einstein,0162</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Samuel Royal Freed on Bond in Einstein Theft</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AUSTIN, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The grandson of former University of Texas
football coach Darrell Royal has been released after being charged
with stealing part of an Albert Einstein manuscript.
   Samuel Royal, 18, who is not a student at the university, was
released Thursday on his personal recognizance from the Travis
County Jail following his arrest Wednesday night.
   Investigators said a telephoned tip led them to the younger
Royal's apartment Tuesday where a page of the manuscript was found
in a photo album, along with photographs of his grandfather, the
University of Texas' football coach from 1957 through 1976.
   ``Sammy is my grandson, and I love him, but I will not attempt
to interfere with the normal process of justice,'' said Darrell
Royal, who now serves as special assistant to the university's
President William Cunningham.
   The felony theft charge carries a maximum punishment of 20 years
in prison.
</TEXT>
