<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   First lady Nancy Reagan was mum after her
look at the $2.5 million Bel Air quarters she and the president
will move to after their lease is up at the White House.
   No one was talking either about how much the first couple is
paying in rent, but the house was purchased for them by Wall
Management Services, a group of about 20 friends of the Reagans.
The group, whose members were not identified, gave the Reagans a
three-year lease with an option to buy, Mrs. Reagan's press
secretary, Elaine Crispen, said earlier this week.
   Mrs. Reagan toured the ranch-style house Thursday.
   It has three bedrooms, six baths, guest room, living room,
family room, sun room, butler's pantry and three servants' rooms.
It is tucked away on a 1\-acre estate in exclusive Bel Air, 12
miles northwest of downtown Los Angeles.
   The Reagans' new neighbors will include Elizabeth Taylor, Joan
Rivers, Zsa Zsa Gabor, Mac Davis and Burt Bacharach.
