Library where the museum is housed.
   ZZ Top members Billy Gibbons, Dusty Hill and Frank Beard will
present a special guitar to the museum, Graves said.
   The group's publicist, Isabel Dassinger, said in New York that
the groups members feel Mississippi bluesman Waters was their
``spiritual godfather.''
