<1ST_LINE>r w BC-McKay-Text 1stLd-Writethru a0671 04-01 0266</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-McKay-Text, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0671,250</2ND_LINE>
<NOTE>Eds: Deletes extraneous word ``or'' and corrects spelling of Aqaba
in 2nd graf, ``James C.''</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   in With AM-Meese Bjt
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the text of the statement issued
Friday by the office of independent counsel James C. McKay
regarding the investigation of Attorney General Edwin Meese III:
   
   James C. McKay, the independent counsel investigating Attorney
General Edwin Meese III, in order to clarify the current status of
this criminal investigation, announced today that, based on the
evidence developed to date, he does not intend to recommend that
the grand jury return an indictment against Mr. Meese as to the
`Aqaba pipeline'' matter or as to the matters relating to Mr.
Meese's investments including the so-called ``Baby Bells'' matter.
   This announcement is being made because of recent media reports
that an indictment is imminent.
   Mr. McKay has previously made a similar announcement with
respect to the Wedtech matter.
   Mr. McKay emphasized, however, that the grand jury's
investigation is not yet complete as to these and other matters,
and will continue at least through the end of April.
   If at the end of that period of time there remains insufficient
evidence to warrant a prosecution as to these or any other matters,
and if the grand jury and the Office of Independent Counsel concur
that further investigation is not warranted, the Office of
Independent Counsel will issue a report covering all the matters
which have been under investigation.
   Also, in that event, Mr. McKay will refer all of those matters
for review and action by the appropriate admnistrative authorities.
</TEXT>
