<HEAD>Thirteen Killed In Bus-Car Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ABIDJAN, Ivory Coast (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus collided with a car and
plummeted into a ravine in an accident that killed 13 people and
injured 42, the government newspaper reported Friday.
   It quoted witnesses as saying the bus swerved to avoid a
bulldozer parked beside the Ivory Coast's main highway Thursday and
met a car head-on.
   The newspaper said four people in the car were killed and a
fifth was injured, and firemen removed nine bodies and 41 injured
people from the bus.
   Accidents are frequent on the highway linking Abidjan, the
country's capital and largest city, with the central city of Bouake.
