<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Mexico-Buses,0107</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Buses Collide, Killing 5 and Injuring 25</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CUAUTLA, Mexico (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two buses collided on a mountain road in
central Mexico Friday, killing five people and injuring 25, highway
police spokesman Jose Manuel Fonseca reported.
   He said both drivers were among the dead in the accident that
occurred at 5:45 a.m. 35 miles southwest of Mexico City on the road
to Oaxaca.
   One bus was from the Red Star firm and the other from the Cargo
and Passenger line, according to Fonseca.
   Fourteen people were killed and 26 injured in a bus accident
Thursday near Valle de Bravo in central Mexico.
</TEXT>
