<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--Stabbings     04-01 0158</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Stabbings,0162</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Manhunt Shuts Highway After Two Killed, Two Wounded</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST CONSHOHOCKEN, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police shut down an expressway
outside Philadelphia on Friday in a search for a man who stabbed to
death two women and wounded a couple working on an archeological
dig at a construction site.
   Police said they knew of no motive for the stabbings, which
occurred in or near a house close to the Schuylkill Expressway, the
state's most congested road and the major east-west thoroughfare
through Philadelphia.
   Authorities withheld information on the dead women but
identified the injured as Glenn Sheehan, 39, and his wife, Ann
Jensen, 31, both hospitalized with multiple stab wounds.
   The shutdown of the expressway for nearly an hour forced a
detour in which a tractor-trailer rammed into two cars and flipped
over a barrier, injuring two people.
   Police said they were looking for a man witnesses described as
driving a pickup truck with Massachusetts license plates.
</TEXT>
