<HEAD>Bus Crash In South Korea Kills 20</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A city bus went out of control while
crossing a bridge and fell 24 feet into the frigid Han river in
Seoul Friday, killing at least 20 people and injuring 40, police
said.
   The bus was carrying some 60 passengers, many of them students
returning home from school, when the driver lost control after one
of the front tires blew out, according to police.
   They said the death toll could rise as divers searched the
partially submerged bus for more bodies.
   Police assisted by passers-by rescued passengers who broke
windows and climbed on top of the bus.
