<HEAD>URGENT</HEAD>
<HEAD>Coup Leader Col. Honasan Escapes From Navy Ship</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The leader of the August coup attempt
that almost toppled the government of President Corazon Aquino
escaped from his prison ship, military sources said Saturday.
   Military spokesmen could not be reached for comment because of
the Easter holiday.
   But sources with ties to leaders of the Aug. 28 attempt said
Col. Gregorio ``Gringo'' Honasan escaped late Friday or early
Saturday. There were no further details.
   Honasan had been detained on a navy ship since his arrest last
December in a Manila suburb.
   One source said officers close to Honasan had been ordered to
report to military Chief of Staff Gen. Renato de Villa to discuss
the case.
   ``Definitely, there is going to be a news blackout,'' the source
said, speaking on condition of anonymity. ``But an officer who
picked up a navy captain and a colonel early this morning said they
were invited for questioning with regards to the escape of Col.
Honasan.''
