<1ST_LINE>r a AM-GangRape     04-01 0479</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Gang Rape,0502</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Town Stunned by Woman's Report of Gang Rape</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOEL WILLIAMS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>SAN DIEGO, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eleven men were charged after a
19-year-old woman told police she was raped repeatedly by a group
of men who urged onlookers at a ranch to join in, authorities said
Thursday.
   Some of the men watching illegal cockfights in a shed nearby
heard the women's cries for help but did nothing; others joined in
the assault Saturday night, said Ricardo Carrillo, Duval County
assistant district attorney.
   ``Some were holding her by the legs and by the arms, and some
were covering her eyes and mouth,'' Carrillo said.
   The woman told authorities that a group of men abducted her half
a block from home and took her to a ranch north of town.
   Authorities believe the woman, who has two children, was
stripped naked and raped repeatedly for several hours in the back
seat of a car, said Carrillo.
   ``Everybody's a little shocked and outraged by it,'' said
assistant district attorney Rodolfo V. Gutierrez.
   Seven men have been charged with sexual assault, three have been
charged with sexual assault and kidnapping and one has been charged
with kidnapping.
   Officials say 20 to 30 men were at the ranch.
   ``A lot of people were present that did not participate, didn't
assault her, but at the same time they didn't do anything to help
her or do anything to stop the other people from assaulting her,''
Gutierrez said.
   ``Even though legally they may not be responsible, morally they
didn't do anything to try and prevent this from happening or to
stop it once it started.''
   He said the woman knew some of her assailants but said some
covered their faces while attacking her.
   ``Some of them we've brought in have admitted it,'' Carrillo
said. ``Some are not talking.''
   Carrillo said the woman was walking home from her uncle's house
when several men abducted her and took her to the ranch.
   The woman reported four men later took her to another location,
raped her again and dropped her off near her home early Sunday,
Carrillo said.
   She was treated at Humana Hospital in Corpus Christi and
released earlier this week, authorities said.
   People in the remote town of about 5,000 are frightened by the
incident, said a 44-year-old woman who asked not to be identified
because in the town ``everybody knows everybody.''
   ``You expect something like this to happen in Corpus or San
Antonio or Dallas, but not in San Diego,'' said the woman.
   All of the men charged are from San Diego, officials said.
   Ten suspects were arrested Wednesday and Thursday or turned
themselves in. At least four were released on bail of $20,000 each.
   One man was not in custody Thursday evening but was expected to
turn himself in, Gutierrez said, adding that there may be more
arrests.
</TEXT>
