<HEAD>GM Takes New York Exhibit on Road</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   General Motors Corp. has decided its high-tech
Teamwork and Technology exhibit was such a hit in New York in
January that it is taking the show on the road.
   The exhibit is scheduled to stop in April 26-27 in Chicago, May
9-10 in Los Angeles, May 23-24 in Dallas, June 6-7 in Atlanta, and
June 13-17 in Warren, Mich.
   At the exhibit, autoworkers, executives and engineers
demonstrated new products, technology and production techniques,
including a working design studio.
   ``We made the point with the New York show that we do have new
products and new technology, and we are making great strides,''
said Jim Crellin, GM's chief spokesman.
   The show also featured concept cars, offering glimpses of the
automotive future, including the Cadillac Voyage. The sleek Voyage
is a four-wheel-drive luxury car with a keyless infrared entry
system and rear-view television.
   The Teamwork and Technology exhibit was held for three days at
New York's Waldorf-Astoria Hotel. Parts of the show have been
displayed in various cities, but most or all of the display will be
reassembled for the new tour.
